Classic use case: creating a packed structures to directly read TCP packets. There is still the &quot;convert from big to little endian&quot; problem, but I think you can use GCC&#x27;s method for individually packing a struct:<p><pre><code>  struct TCP_Packet {
    uint16_t source_port;
    uint16_t dest_port;
    uint32_t seq_no;
    uint16_t flags;
    uint16_t window_size;
    uint16_t checksum;
    unit16_t urgent;
    ...
  }  __attribute__ ((packed));</code></pre>
